{"decision_id":"rel-trt-construction-second-ave","verdict":"fail","failure_reason":"The cited blocks do not establish that the construction zone is a treatment OF the First/Second Avenue SBS project. p029_c0007 appears on a page explicitly headed 'Second Avenue Subway construction' (p029 block 2), revealing the construction zone belongs to the Second Avenue Subway (SAS) project, not the SBS project. The text states 'NYCT and DOT are working with SAS team to: Eliminate SBS station/routing conflicts' — the SBS project is coordinating around an external construction zone, not implementing it as its own treatment. The cited blocks merely list the zone's location (p026_c0010-11) and state no changes are planned there (p029_c0007). Co-occurrence in the SBS presentation does not constitute a stated 'has_treatment' relation.","evidence_checked":["2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p026_c0010","2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p026_c0011","2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p029_c0007","2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p029_c0002","2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p024_c0003","2010_03_11_brt_1st2nd_cb8#p035_c0004"]}
